         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 2654, recto: (1) Psemmonthes, son of Pasemis, son of [Meswer], has paid (2) to the bank of the northern houses for the silver (3) of poll of year 33 in Jeme, 2 staters / (4) 1 stater / 2 staters again. Written in year 33, (5) Pharmouthi 14. Likewise, on Epiphi (6) 11, for the silver of poll of year 33, 2 staters (7) / 1 stater / 2 staters again. Likewise, for the bath (8) (tax) of year 33, 1 kite.</ab>
